God is on the move! For 7 days straight, around the clock, people from all over have been lining up outside at Asbury University to experience the PRESENCE of GOD! Salvations, radical repentance, worship, prayer, and deliverance are all taking place. No preaching, so far…no big names…no personal promotion…no human agenda…JUST JESUS! 

So when we heard what God was doing, we cleared our schedules and went. 

His presence can be pursued anywhere, but there are times when His glory descends in a specific place at a specific time, and I’ve committed myself to be a God-chaser! Let’s be pursuers of His presence!

Feel free to tune in LIVE at https://www.youtube.com/live/D_U7uXBEkFg?feature=share

The parent must not provoke them to anger - Ephesians 6:4.

This can happen very quickly by not having a strong relationship with them and by just giving them rules without processing the rules with your child. How many times we have heard a parent say, “Because I said so!” We wouldn’t treat our spouse or our employees with that kind of language. That is not honoring and loving your child.
 
THE PARENT MUST DISCIPLINE THEM.

Ephesians 6:4b but bring them up in the discipline and instruction of the Lord.
Proverbs 13:24 He who withholds his rod hates his son, but he who loves him disciplines him diligently.
Proverbs 22:15 Foolishness is bound up in the heart of a child; The rod of discipline will remove it far from him.

HOW TO DISCIPLINE EFFECTIVELY
The ground rules must be clear. E.g., “If you cross the street without daddy and mommy watching you, you will be spanked.”

Never discipline in anger. Calm down and allow the fruit of the Spirit of self-control to grace you before you spank.
Use a neutral object, like a wooden spoon with a flat end. You don’t want to use your hands. Your hands should be used for love and affection.

You must restore them after the spanking with prayer. Have your child repeat after you: “Jesus, forgive me for disobeying daddy and mommy.”

Pronounce that Jesus forgives them, and daddy and mommy forgive them.

Finally, hug and kiss them.

The devil opposes anything that’s of God, especially when it’s done boldly and with Godly confidence.

If you’re ever wondering what God’s heart is for something, see what the enemy is trying to do in that area, and then think of the complete opposite and that’s God’s heart.

The enemy wants to confuse, while the Lord wants to bring clarity. The enemy wants to destroy, while the Lord wants to build up. The enemy wants people to be insecure about their identity, while the Lord wants people to walk in Godly confidence as a child of God.

God’s heart is always for His people.

Do you want this in your home? Say AMEN, if you do! I’ve listed some ideas for you below.

First off, Ephesians 5:18 “And do not get drunk with wine, for that is dissipation, but be filled with the Spirit.”

Be filled continually. The Greek verb is in the continuous present tense. It is also a command. God knows that we cannot develop the fruit of the Spirit without being full of the Holy Spirit (Galatians 5:22).

To be filled is to be controlled and led by the Holy Spirit. There is one baptism but many fillings. Every day, ask God to fill you with the Holy Spirit. Let the Spirit of God control your mind and your emotions.

Be led by the Holy Spirit. “How can I love my wife/husband today, or at this moment?”

How do you really do this? WELL…we come to a passage in Paul’s Ephesian letter of truth that has helped me immensely: the principle of putting off and putting on. For example, to put off is a practical way of repenting.

But to put on is coming in the opposite spirit by putting on biblical values through meditating on God’s Word.

PUTTING OFF OLD SELF - Ephesians 4:17 “So this I say, and affirm together with the Lord, that you walk no longer just as the Gentiles also walk, in the futility of their mind, being darkened in their understanding, excluded from the life of God because of the ignorance that is in them, because of the hardness of their heart; and they, having become callous, have given themselves over to sensuality for the practice of every kind of impurity with greediness. But you did not learn Christ in this way, if indeed you have heard Him and have been taught in Him, just as truth is in Jesus, that, in reference to your former manner of life, you lay aside the old self, which is being corrupted in accordance with the lusts of deceit.”

 PUTTING ON THE NEW SELF:Ephesians 4:23 and that you be renewed in the spirit of your mind, and put on the new self, which in the likeness of God has been created in righteousness and holiness of the truth.

Friendship evangelism is loving and befriending those who don’t know Jesus that God brings into your life. It is the way you relate to the lost.

Winkie Pratney said it this way, “You are a witness to whatever or whoever is foremost in your life. You are telling the world right now what god you really belong to. Your words and your life are tied inseparably together; you will always convey to others around you what you really love and live for most. Your words will either prove this or call you a liar.
